{{Ada/Navigation|Delimiters|2= ..}}
{{wrongtitle|title=Ada Programming/Delimiters/..}}
__TOC__

The [[Ada Programming/Delimiters|delimiter]] '''..''' is used to specify [[Ada Programming/Types/range|ranges]] in any [[Ada Programming/Types|scalar type]].

For example:

* In numeric type definitions:
 {{Ada/kw|type}} Count {{Ada/kw|is}} {{Ada/kw|range}} 0 '''..''' Max_Count;

* In [[Ada Programming/Subtypes#Declaring subtypes|subtype]] definitions:
 {{Ada/kw|subtype}} Week_Day {{Ada/kw|is}} Day_Name {{Ada/kw|range}} Monday '''..''' Friday;

* In [[Ada Programming/Variables|variable]] declarations:
 Vector_A : Vector (0 '''..''' 31);

* In [[Ada Programming/Operators#Membership tests|membership tests]]:
 {{Ada/kw|exit}} {{Ada/kw|when}} X {{Ada/kw|in}} Y '''..''' Y + Epsilon;

* In [[Ada Programming/Control#loops|for loops]]:
 {{Ada/kw|for}} Day {{Ada/kw|in}} Day_Name {{Ada/kw|range}} Monday '''..''' Thursday {{Ada/kw|loop}}
    {{Ada/--|...}}
 {{Ada/kw|end}} {{Ada/kw|loop}};

* In [[Ada Programming/Types/array|arrays]]:
 Vector_A (Vector_A'{{Ada/attribute|First}} .. Vector_A'{{Ada/attribute|First}} + Vector_B'{{Ada/attribute|Length}} - 1) := Vector_B;

== Usage notes ==

When a whole type range will be specified, it is better to use the {{Ada/attribute|Range}} attribute.

For example, instead of using:

 {{Ada/kw|for}} Day {{Ada/kw|in}} {{Ada/kw|range}} Day_Name'{{Ada/attribute|First}} '''..''' Day_Name'{{Ada/attribute|Last}} {{Ada/kw|loop}}
    {{Ada/--|...}}
 {{Ada/kw|end}} {{Ada/kw|loop}};

it is better to use:

 {{Ada/kw|for}} Day {{Ada/kw|in}} Day_Name'{{Ada/attribute|Range}} {{Ada/kw|loop}}
    {{Ada/--|...}}
 {{Ada/kw|end}} {{Ada/kw|loop}};

